<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4454796-fernando-cabral"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1287887499i/4454796._UX100_CR0,4,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4454796-fernando-cabral">Fernando Cabral</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Hey Eva! kinda of late here (answering a question from 1 year ago haha), but let&apos;s go!<br/>I didn&apos;t read all the books yet (though I already purchased them<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Hey Eva! kinda of late here (answering a question from 1 year ago haha), but let's go!<br />I didn't read all the books yet (though I already purchased them), but I know that all of the books are from the Lestat's point of view, except the ones from the "New Tales of the Vampires", which there're 2 books, one in the point of view of Pandora and the other in the pov of Vittorio.<br /><br />So there isn't any book in the David Talbot's pov (unfortunately). <br />Until this 4th book David had only appeared a few times, not having much participation. Now with this 4th book (specially after the conclusion with David Talbot in the book), I think he'll have more participation in the next books. I know that in the Lives of the Mayfair Witches' crossover books (Merrick, Blackwood Farm and Blood Canticle) David Talbot will have a important role.<br /><br />I just finish this 4th book and will start the Lives of Mayfair Witches before continuing in the Vampire Chronicles, so soon I'll have more info about it! <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
