  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1883039190" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1883039190" />
    <a title="Jess The Bookworm" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32042916-jess-the-bookworm"><img alt="Jess The Bookworm" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1454940122p2/32042916.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1883039190?book_show_action=true">Aug 01, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jess The Bookworm" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jess The Bookworm" href="/user/show/32042916-jess-the-bookworm">Jess The Bookworm</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1883039190" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2219323412886548201">Lestat returns, in this the fourth novel in the Vampire Chronicles. Lestat, always one looking for trouble, always philosophizing, meets with a Body Thief: a man capable of switching bodies with other people, most of the time against their will. <br/><br/>Lestat agrees to switch bodies with this Body Thief for one day, so that he can feel what it is like to be human again.<br/><br/>As one expects, everything does not go as plan, and Lestat has to try and get himself out of the dangerous position he has put himself </span>
  <span id="freeText2219323412886548201" style="display:none">Lestat returns, in this the fourth novel in the Vampire Chronicles. Lestat, always one looking for trouble, always philosophizing, meets with a Body Thief: a man capable of switching bodies with other people, most of the time against their will. <br /><br />Lestat agrees to switch bodies with this Body Thief for one day, so that he can feel what it is like to be human again.<br /><br />As one expects, everything does not go as plan, and Lestat has to try and get himself out of the dangerous position he has put himself in.<br /><br />I thoroughly enjoyed the descriptions of Lestat's rediscovery of human life, although it made being human suddenly seem disgusting to me, and made me, much like Lestat, wish to be the immortal undead. <br /><br />This was another wonderful foray into Lestat's psyche and his world, and I am still immensely enthralled by this series. <br /><br />I am a little bit apprehensive about the next one, being Memnoch the Devil, given some of the reviews which I have read on here, but I am still going to give it a bash.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2219323412886548201" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1883039190">
